IEEE XPlore Innovation Spotlight: “Knowing All the Bio-Signals: New Wearable Device Could Improve Health Care” (co-authored by Amir M. Rahmani)
November 28, 2017 A team of international researchers has designed a new device that could make your next hospital stay easier for you and your doctor. Researchers from the University of Turku and the University of California proposed a wearable device that can remotely monitor a patient’s vital signs and pain levels, potentially enabling doctors to address patient issues quicker and less intrusively.
Read the full story at IEEE XPlore Innovation Spotlight.
